    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-23T03:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-23T03:35:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War, 1939/26691: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-23T12:00:00+03:25"
                            >December 23, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 8:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>458. My 341, October 25.<note n="72" xml:id="d443fn72">Not printed.</note>
                    Foreign Minister informs me both he and Prime Minister strongly desire to have
                    Iran adhere to United Nations Declaration.<note n="73" xml:id="d443fn73">Signed
                        at Washington, January 1, 1942, <ref target="frus1942v01#pg_25">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1942, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 25</ref>.</note> He stated that they are
                    working on public opinion in order to prepare for such a step which they hope
                    can be taken within several months.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
